description:
Job Responsibilities

Develop and implement sales strategy to drive business growth;
Promote medical brand(s) to potential clients in Ethical Sectors;
Build strong network and maintain good relationship with medical professionals and key opinion leaders within the community for lead generation;
Collaborate with customers to create win-win relationship for both parties’ business growth;
Ensure timely and effective implementation of sales and marketing strategies to achieve sales target;
Actively share market insights and collaborate with Brand team to sharpen sales conversion tactics;
Maintain effective communication and good working relations with teammates, Brand team and other related departments to ensure smooth operation;
Provide support for medical conference and seminars and seek for lead generation opportunities;
Work independently with well-planned work schedules and weekly timetables.

Requirements

Bachelor’s Degree in Pharmacy, Life Sciences, Pharmacology or related discipline;
3-5 years of sales experience in pharmaceutical industry;
Fluent in spoken and written English and Chinese;
Good communication, presentation, negotiation and interpersonal skills;
Detail-orientated, self-motivated, good team player;
Energetic and open-minded;
Proficient in Microsoft Office (Excel, PowerPoint, Outlook);
Less experienced candidate will be considered as Senior Medical Specialist.

Working Location: Hong Kong Science Park, Tai Po, N.T.

We offer 5-day working week and an attractive remuneration package. Interested party please submit your resume with current and expected salary by clicking “APPLY NOW”. For company details, please visit www.purapharm.com.

Our company is an equal opportunity employer. All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only, while the personal data of the unsuccessful applicants will be destroyed within 6 months after the recruitment process.

Responsibilities

- Provide high standard tenancy services;

- Front-desk and concierge operation at Grade A Commercial Building;

- Handle customers’ inquiries and complaints, crown control, prepare reports and involve in  ad-hoc duties assigned;

- Coordinate with other departments on the execution of day-to-day commercial building operations and activities.

Requirement

- Diploma or above;

- Pleasant, self-motivated, responsive and able to work independently;

- Excellent telephone manner and customer service mindset;

- Good communication and presentation skills;

- Good command in spoken and written English, Cantonese, and Mandarin; 

Benefit: Double Pay, Medical Insurance, Dental Insurance, Public Holiday

Please send application enclosing resume stating career and salary history, expected salary and date of availability to us by clicking “Apply Now”.

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data collected will be treated in strictest confidence and handled confidentially by authorized personnel for recruitment-related purposes within the Group. Applicants not hearing from us within six weeks from the date of advertisement may consider their applications unsuccessful.

A multinational consumer goods company with global presence is looking for an Associate Director to join their logistics & operations team. The successful candidate will lead a sizable team in customer service, logistics and operation functions. 

The Position
This position will oversee the company's e-commerce, retail business operations and logistics functions. The successful candidate will partner with major stakeholders within all functional departments to drive business growth and enhance customer experience by offering best platforms from online to offline.


Managing the performance of 3PL to ensure all KPIs are met;
Explore new ways and best practices to reduce costs, improve service quality and reduce operational risk;
Manage the execution and completion of the defined project plans/ roadmaps through effectively coordinating people and resources that support annual business, financial and growth objectives;
Support business opportunities in compliance with global operational strategies. 

Requirement


Bachelor degree or above in supply chain, operations or any related discipline;
Minimum 10 years of managerial experience in which 5 years’ experience in logistics and customer service field;
Experience in O2O operation and leading service team;
Being proactive with strong interpersonal skills to communicate with different customers and colleagues;
Strong leadership with strategical thinking to achieve operational and customer service excellence.

 (All personal data collected will be kept confidential and is for recruitment purpose only.)
